This paper deals with the problem of link prediction in Knowledge Bases, which involves using machine learning models to predict missing relationships between entities in a directed graph. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Given that the paper proposes a novel approach that combines two different types of embedding models, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these sub-fields.
